Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil
with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the
@red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}.

Halve any large @cauliflower florets{300%g}. Pop the florets onto a
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for the flour}, season with @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{} then sprinkle over the @Italian style herbs{1}. Toss to coat then
spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf
until golden and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and
bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain
in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{for the pasta}
and stir through to stop it sticking together. While the pasta cooks, pop the
@panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into a #medium bowl{} and add the
@olive oil{for the crumb}(for the crumb). Season with salt and pepper, mix
together, then set aside.

Heat the @olive oil{for the roux}(for the roux) in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add in the onion and cook until
softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Then stir in the @plain flour{16%g} and cook until it
forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux! Gradually stir in the
@water{250%ml} and the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stir
and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g},
then remove from the heat.

Add the Cheddar to the sauce and stir until melted. Taste and add salt and
pepper if needed. Stir the cooked pasta and roasted cauliflower through the
sauce with a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Spoon into a
#medium-sized ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle the crumbs evenly over the top.
Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the pasta bakes, pop the @cider vinegar{15%ml} into a medium bowl with
the @olive oil{for the dressing}(for the dressing) and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}.
Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Once the pasta bake is cooked,
add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the dressing and toss to coat. Serve the
cauliflower rigatoni cheese with the salad alongside. Enjoy!

> STEP 4 MOD: If you've added bacon lardons to your recipe, add the oil to the
> pan as instructed in the step above, then add the bacon lardons. Stir-fry until
> golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
> handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly. Add the onion to the pan with the
> lardons and continue with the step as instructed.

-- Ingredients for optional bacon lardons:
-- @?British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}
-- For the crumb:
-- @gluten free breadcrumbs{50%g} can be used instead of panko breadcrumbs.
-- For dressing:
-- @plain flour{1.5%g} used in some variations _not_ in original recipe but listed in ingredients.